00:00:12.990 --> 00:00:15.540
So what on earth are these basal norms?

00:00:16.155 --> 00:00:21.645
Think of them as the strict universally
agreed upon rules set by the big boss

00:00:21.645 --> 00:00:27.314
of international banking, the Basal
Committee on Banking Supervision, or BCBS.

00:00:27.884 --> 00:00:32.625
The main goal, my friend, is to make
sure our banks don't go on a wild

00:00:32.625 --> 00:00:35.505
lending spree without any backup cash.

00:00:36.045 --> 00:00:40.725
These norms ensure banks have
enough capital a safety net to

00:00:40.725 --> 00:00:43.485
absorb unexpected shocks and losses.

00:00:43.970 --> 00:00:49.010
This protects us the depositors and
keeps the whole financial system from

00:00:49.010 --> 00:00:50.510
collapsing like a house of cards.

00:00:51.555 --> 00:00:56.205
Now these aren't legally binding
laws that will land a banker in jail.

00:00:56.505 --> 00:01:00.585
Instead, they are super strong
recommendations that countries,

00:01:00.735 --> 00:01:05.325
including our own India, via
the RBI adopt and enforce.

00:01:05.805 --> 00:01:07.575
It's like a Bollywood franchise.

00:01:07.845 --> 00:01:13.815
