00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:33.440
The most important formula is for
the capital adequacy ratio or CAR.

00:03:33.770 --> 00:03:38.690
It is total capital, which is tier
one plus tier two capital divided

00:03:38.690 --> 00:03:43.340
by the risk weighted assets, or
RWA, all multiplied by a hundred.

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:48.170
Remember, tier one capital is the
bank's core, high quality capital,

00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:50.510
like its own equity and profits.

00:03:50.805 --> 00:03:52.905
It's the bank's own hard earned money.

00:03:53.610 --> 00:03:54.120
Tier two.

00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:58.500
Capital is the supplementary stuff
like reserves and subordinated debt

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:04.290
and risk weighted assets, or RWA is a
clever concept where a bank's assets

00:04:04.290 --> 00:04:06.480
are weighted by how risky they are.

00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:10.650
A loan to the government is less
risky than a personal loan, so

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:12.210
it gets a lower risk weight.

00:04:12.780 --> 00:04:13.950
Here's a trick to remember.

