00:04:36.390 --> 00:04:38.610
Now how to solve problems with this?

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:45.150
Let's look at method one, calculating the
capital adequacy ratio First, identify and

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:47.670
add up all tier one capital components.

00:04:47.880 --> 00:04:51.000
Second, do the same for
all tier two components.

00:04:51.305 --> 00:04:55.775
Third, calculate total capital by
adding tier one and two together.

00:04:56.075 --> 00:04:59.045
Fourth, determine the
total risk weighted assets.

00:04:59.344 --> 00:05:02.915
This means you multiply each
asset's value by its risk

00:05:02.915 --> 00:05:04.625
percentage and sum them all up.

00:05:04.895 --> 00:05:07.325
Finally, apply the CAR formula.

00:05:07.475 --> 00:05:12.395
Divide your total capital by the
total RWA and multiply by a hundred.

