00:06:37.705 --> 00:06:39.685
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:43.560
Let's talk about the common
traps people fall into first.

00:06:43.770 --> 00:06:45.930
Don't confuse tier one and tier two.

00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:47.850
Capital tier one is core.

00:06:47.970 --> 00:06:49.530
Tier two is supplementary.

00:06:49.740 --> 00:06:52.200
Second, don't mix up the three pillars.

00:06:52.350 --> 00:06:53.910
Their functions are distinct.

00:06:54.300 --> 00:06:58.320
A very common mistake is thinking
basal norms are actual laws.

00:06:58.470 --> 00:06:59.370
They are not.

00:06:59.700 --> 00:07:03.480
They are recommendations which
national regulators, like RBI

00:07:03.750 --> 00:07:05.310
turn into mandatory rules.

00:07:05.680 --> 00:07:08.140
Also, don't forget about risk weights.

00:07:08.260 --> 00:07:13.390
Not all assets are equal, and please
don't overlook liquidity and leverage.

00:07:13.570 --> 00:07:17.140
Basal three made a huge deal
about these, and they are separate

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:18.850
from just capital adequacy.

